## 9. Implementation Roadmap

### Phase 1: Hybrid Search (Day 1-2)
```
1. Add search_vector column + trigger to database     -> 30 min
2. Create hybrid_search.py service                    -> 1 hour
3. Update rag_service.py to use hybrid search          -> 30 min
4. Test with existing documents                        -> 30 min
5. Tune vector_weight / keyword_weight                 -> 1 hour
```

### Phase 2: Streaming LLM (Day 2-3)
```
1. Add generate_rag_response_stream() to llm_service   -> 1 hour
2. Create /chat/stream endpoint with SSE               -> 1 hour
3. Update ChatBox.tsx to consume SSE stream             -> 2 hours
4. Add fallback for non-streaming browsers              -> 30 min
5. Test end-to-end streaming                            -> 30 min
```

### Phase 3: RAGAS Evaluation (Day 3-4)
```
1. pip install ragas datasets langchain-google-genai    -> 10 min
2. Create eval_service.py with sample dataset           -> 1 hour
3. Create /eval/run endpoint                            -> 30 min
4. Run first evaluation and analyze scores              -> 1 hour
5. Create custom eval dataset for your domain           -> 2 hours
6. Build eval results dashboard (optional)              -> 2 hours
```

### Priority Order

**Implement in this order for maximum impact:**
1. **Hybrid Search** — Immediately improves retrieval quality (biggest ROI)
2. **Streaming** — Transforms user experience from "waiting" to "interactive"
3. **RAGAS Evaluation** — Gives you data to systematically improve the system

---

> **Note:** All code examples are designed to work with the existing KnowBase AI codebase. Each feature includes backward-compatible fallbacks so you can implement them incrementally without breaking the current system.
